        "content": "          \u003ctitle\u003eMasonry layout - CSS | MDN\u003c/title\u003e\n   \u003cmeta name=\"description\" content=\"Level 3 of the CSS grid layout specification defines masonry layout (also known as grid-lanes layout), which is accessed via the display values grid-lanes and inline-grid-lanes. This guide details what masonry layout is and how to use it.\" /\u003e\u003cmeta name=\"og:url\" content=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Guides/Grid_layout/Masonry_layout\" /\u003e\u003cmeta name=\"og:title\" content=\"Masonry layout - CSS | MDN\" /\u003e\u003cmeta name=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" /\u003e\u003cmeta name=\"og:description\" content=\"Level 3 of the CSS grid layout specification defines masonry layout (also known as grid-lanes layout), which is accessed via the display values grid-lanes and inline-grid-lanes. This guide details what masonry layout is and how to use it.\" /\u003e\u003cmeta name=\"og:image\" content=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/mdn-social-image.46ac2375.png\" /\u003e\u003cmeta name=\"og:image:type\" content=\"image/png\" /\u003e\u003cmeta name=\"og:image:height\" content=\"1024\" /\u003e\u003cmeta name=\"og:image:width\" content=\"1024\" /\u003e\u003cmeta name=\"og:image:alt\" content=\"The MDN logo\" /\u003e\u003cmeta name=\"og:site_name\" content=\"MDN Web Docs\" /\u003e\u003cmeta name=\"twitter:card\" content=\"summary\" /\u003e\u003cmeta name=\"twitter:creator\" content=\"MozDevNet\" /\u003e\n            href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Guides/Grid_layout/Masonry_layout\"\n      \u003c!--lit-part ijtgkDNyZhc=--\u003e\u003csvg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m21 21-4.34-4.34\"/\u003e\u003ccircle cx=\"11\" cy=\"11\" r=\"8\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c!--/lit-part--\u003e\n      \u003c!--lit-part ij